        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2013-08-05 20:45:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI don't understand why there is all of this confusion about which FID the progress is occurring on. Isn't the progress on the action which is identified by the cookie? It seems that sending back the FIDs along with the cookie there is now some choice about how to identify an action. Which is bad.",
