        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2013-08-06 09:11:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.4/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/8805ae18-fe69-11e2-afbf-52540035b04c).  Ran 16 tests.  6 tests failed: sanity-hsm, lustre-rsync-test, conf-sanity, replay-single, sanityn, sanity.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "3985712f2e2c38807ba51aac480184fdeb4d694b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 263,
        "name": "Henri Doreau",
        "email": "henri.doreau@cea.fr",
        "username": "hdoreau"
      },
      "date": "2013-08-06 09:21:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nBecause the MDT used to create the volatile file its client interface was not originally designed to receive the restore data FID. This FID is needed by the coordinator so that it can eventually do the final layout swap. We pass both the FID and the cookie to double-check consistency.\n\nAdditionally, the copytool API was perceived and designed as something for external users who'd need to write their own copytools. As such, we're looking for the simplest possible API.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
